Package me.taylorkelly.mywarp.command.parametric.annotation

  • Annotation Types Summary 
    Annotation Type Description
    Billable
    Annotates a method that withdraws a certain fee from callers once executed successfully.
    Modifiable
    Indicates that a warp specified by a command argument must be modifiable by the command sender.
    Sender
    Indicates that the required parameter is in fact the sender of the command and should be acquired from the command's Namespace.
    Usable
    Indicates that a warp specified by a command argument must be usable by the command sender.
    Viewable
    Indicates that a warp specified by a command argument must be viewable by the command sender.
    WarpName
    Indicates that a String value should be used as a name for a Warp instance.
